door_types.description: Door type documentation with parameter meanings

HasRuneDoor.description: Requires player to have a specific rune to pass through

MinimumRuneDoor.description: Requires player to have at least a minimum rune level

PrivateRoomDoor.description: Limits number of players allowed in target room

ItemKeyDoor.description: Requires player to have a specific item to pass

LevelDoor.description: Requires player to be a specific level

ClassDoor.description: Requires player to be a specific class

rooms.long_description:
You are standing in an enormous stone chamber, fitted with reddish brown
flagstones, unlike the dull grey stones in the outer corridors. The room is
octagonal in shape, and huge smouldering censers burn in the corners. The
only visible exit is northwest through an ornate stone archway.

room_flags.note: Bitwise OR of flag values from _enumerations.room_flags

rooms.long_description:
You are standing in a well kept flagstone corridor. The stonework here is
of the finest quality, and certain of the stones are engraved with a luniform
design. There is a jagged hole in the ceiling, and rubble litters the floor.
The corridor leads to the south.
